If you know all the arguments are numbers, an easy way is a little comprehension.

```
def __num__(*args):
    if any([arg for arg in args if arg &gt; 10]):
        print(&#39;I am testing args using {}&#39;.format(args[&#39;x&#39;]))
    else :
        print(&#39;Something Goes Wrong&#39;)
